 dello sbarco | url=https://www.panorama.it/news/cronaca/6-giugno-1944-italiani-normandia-d-day/ | website=www.panorama.it | accessdate=31 December 2019 | language=Italian | date=7 June 2019 | ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book | last = Gaddis | first = John Lewis | authorlink = John Lewis Gaddis | title = Russia, the Soviet Union, and the United States: An Interpretive History | year = 1990 | origyear = 1972 | publisher = McGraw-Hill | location = New York | isbn = 978-0-07-557258-9 | ref = harv | url = https://archive.org/details/russiasovietunio00gadd }}\n* {{cite book | last1 = Giangreco | first1 = Dennis | authorlink1 = Dennis Giangreco | last2 = Moore | first2 = Kathryn | last3 = Polmar | first3 = Norman | author3link = Norman Polmar | title = Eyewitness D-Day: Firsthand Accounts from the Landing at Normandy to the Liberation of Paris | year = 2004 | publisher = Barnes & Noble | location = New York | isbn = 978-0-7607-5045-2 | ref = harv | url = https://archive.org/details/eyewitnessddayfi00gian_0 }}\n* {{cite book | last = Gilbert | first = Martin | authorlink = Martin Gilbert | title = The Second World War: A Complete History | year = 1989 | publisher = H. Holt | location = New York | isbn = 978-0-8050-1788-5 | ref = harv | url = https://archive.org/details/secondworldwar00gilb }}\n* {{cite book | last1 = Goldstein | first1 = Donald M. | last2 = Dillon | first2 = Katherine V. | last3 = Wenger | first3 = J. Michael | title = D-Day: The Story and Photographs | year = 1994 | publisher = Brassey's | location = McLean, Virginia | isbn = 0-02-881057-0 | ref = harv}}\n* {{cite web | author = Government of Luxembourg | title = Les Luxembourgeois de la \"Brigade Piron\" |trans-title=The Luxembourg \"Brigade Piron\" | language = French | url = http://www.armee.lu/historique/les-luxembourgeois-de-la-brigade-piron | accessdate = 28 March 2017 | ref = {{sfnRef|Luxembourg Army website}} }}\n* {{cite book | last = Hastings | first = Max | authorlink = Max Hastings | title = Overlord: D-Day and the Battle for Normandy | year = 2006 | origyear = 1985 | publisher = Vintage | location = New York | isbn = 0-307-27571-X | ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book | last = Horn | first = Bernd | title = Men of Steel: Canadian Paratroopers in Normandy, 1944 | year = 2010 | publisher = Dundurn Press | location = Toronto, CA | isbn = 978-1-55488-708-8 | ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book | last = Hughes | first = Thomas Alexander | title = Overlord: General Pete Quesada and the Triumph of Tactical A | year = 2010 | publisher = Simon and Schuster | location = New York City, NY | isbn = 978-1-43911-853-5 | ref = harv}}\n* {{cite journal |last1 = Liedtke | first1 = Gregory | title = Lost in the Mud: The (Nearly) Forgotten Collapse of the German Army in the Western Ukraine, March and April 1944 | journal = The Journal of Slavic Military Studies | date = 2 January 2015 | volume = 28 | issue = 1 | pages = 215\u2013238 | doi = 10.1080/13518046.2015.998134 | issn = 1351-8046 | ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book | last = Pogue | first = Forrest C. | authorlink = Forrest Pogue | title = United States Army in World War II: European Theater of Operations: The Supreme Command | chapter = Chapter XIV: The Pursuit Stops Short of the Rhine | year = 1954 | publisher = Office of the Chief of Military History, Department of the Army | location = Washington, D.C. | lccn = 53-61717 | chapter-url = http://www.ibiblio.org/hyperwar/USA/USA-E-Supreme/USA-E-Supreme-14.html#fn10 | ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book | last = Shulman | first = Milton | authorlink = Milton Shulman | title = Defeat in the West | year = 2007 | origyear = 1947 | publisher = Kessinger | location = Whitefish, Montana | isbn = 978-0-548-43948-7 | ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book | last = Stacey | first = C.P. | authorlink = Charles Perry Stacey | title = The Canadian Army 1939\u201345: A Historical Summary | year = 1948 | publisher = Published by Authority of the Minister of National Defence | location = Ottawa\n | url = http://www.ibiblio.or