ed Champion: The Top Tanks of World War II | year = 2015 | publisher = Stackpole Books | location = Mechanicsburg, PA | isbn = 978-0-8117-6113-0 | ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book | last = Zetterling | first = Niklas | title = Normandy 1944: German Military Organisation, Combat Power and Organizational Effectiveness | year = 2000 | publisher = [[J.J. Fedorowicz Publishing|J.J. Fedorowicz]] | location = Winnipeg | isbn = 0-921991-56-8 | ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book | last = Zuehlke | first = Mark | title = Juno Beach: Canada's D-Day Victory: June 6, 1944 | year = 2004 | publisher = Douglas & McIntyre | location = Vancouver | isbn = 1-55365-050-6 | ref = harv}}\n{{refend}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n{{refbegin|30em}}\n* {{cite book | last = Ambrose | first = Stephen E. | authorlink = Stephen E. Ambrose | title = The Supreme Commander: The War Years of General Dwight D. Eisenhower | year = 1969 | publisher = Doubleday | location = Garden City, New York | oclc = 660826327 }}\n* {{cite book | last = Foot | first = M. R. D. | authorlink = M. R. D. Foot | title = SOE: An Outline History of the Special Operations Executive 1940\u20131946 | year = 1984 | publisher = BBC Publications | location = London | isbn = 978-0-563-20193-9}}\n* {{cite book | last = Keegan | first = John | authorlink = John Keegan | title = Six Armies in Normandy | year = 1982 | publisher = Penguin Books | location = New York | isbn = 978-0-14-005293-0}}\n* {{cite book | last=Lewis | first=Nigel | title=Exercise Tiger: The Dramatic True Story of a Hidden Tragedy of World War II | publisher=Prentice-Hall | location=New York | year=1990 | isbn=0-13-127796-0 | ref=harv | url=https://archive.org/details/exercisetigerdra00lewi }}\n* {{cite book | last = Matloff | first = Maurice | title = Strategic Planning for Coalition Warfare, 1943\u20131944 | year = 1959 | publisher = Center of Military History, United States Army | location = Washington | url =https://history.army.mil/books/wwii/sp1943-44/index.htm }}\n* {{cite book | last = Montgomery | first = Bernard | authorlink = Bernard Montgomery, 1st Viscount Montgomery of Alamein | title = Normandy to the Baltic | year = 1946 | publisher = Hutchinson | location = London | oclc = 637320842}}\n* {{cite book | last = Neillands | first = Robin | authorlink = Robin Neillands | title = The Battle of Normandy, 1944 | year = 2002 | publisher = Cassell | location = London | isbn = 978-0-304-35837-3 | url = https://archive.org/details/battleofnormandy0000neil }}\n* {{cite book | last = Ryan | first = Cornelius | authorlink = Cornelius Ryan | title = The Longest Day: June 6, 1944 | year = 1959 | publisher = Simon & Schuster | location = New York | oclc = 1175409| title-link = The Longest Day (book) }}\n* {{cite book | last = Whitlock | first = Flint | title = The Fighting First: The Untold Story of The Big Red One on D-Day | year = 2004 | publisher = Westview | location = Boulder | isbn = 978-0-8133-4218-4 | url = https://archive.org/details/fightingfirst00flin }}\n* {{cite book|last = Zaloga|first = Steven|title = Operation Cobra 1944: Breakout from Normandy| series = Osprey Campaign Series #88|year = 2001|publisher = Osprey|location = Oxford|isbn = 978-1-84176-296-8 }}\n{{refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category|Battle of Normandy|''Overlord''}}\n* {{OL subject|operation_overlord}}\n* {{Worldcat subject|lccn-sh85095004}}\n\n{{World War II}}\n{{Battle of Normandy}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{good article}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Overlord}}\n[[Category:1944 in France]]\n[[Category:August 1944 events]]\n[[Category:Battles and operations of World War II involving France]]\n[[Category:Battles and operations of World War II involving Germany]]\n[[Category:Battles and operations of World War II involving the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Battles and operations of World War II involving the United States]]\n[[Category:Battles of World War II involving Canada]]\n[[Category:Conflicts in 1944]]\n[[Category:Invasions by Australia]]\n[[Category